  <LINE>Council, with the Ministers of the ten Established</LINE>
  <LINE>churches of Glasgow, patrons; Laurence Hill, LL.B.,</LINE>
  <LINE>1 South Frederick Street, chamberlain; J. Macarley</LINE>
  <LINE>and G. H. M'Millan, teachers ; Hugh Gibson, music</LINE>
  <LINE>master ; Alexander Gemmill, baron officer.</LINE>
  <LINE>THE BISHOP'S SCHOOL,</LINE>
  <LINE>Waterloo Street.</LINE>
  <LINE>This school was erected by the congregation of</LINE>
  <LINE>St. Mary's Episcopal Church for the religious educa-</LINE>
  <LINE>tion of the children of the poorer members of the</LINE>
  <LINE>Episcopal communion. It is supported by congrega-</LINE>
  <LINE>tional subscriptions, and is managed by a committee.</LINE>
  <LINE>It is under government inspection.</LINE>
